## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Medium-soft (feels around 42-44 degrees ESN scale).
    - Feedback: Clear and vibration-rich. You can feel exactly when the ball engages the sponge.
    - Hold vs. Release: Excellent hold. The ball feels like it sits on the racket face for a long time before being launched.
    - Dwell Time: Extremely high.

- Sound/Click
Produces a very satisfying, sharp click or metallic crack on moderate to hard impacts, reminiscent of speed-glued rubbers, largely due to the #80 macro-porous sponge.

